Diagram 1 — ERD voor een bibliotheek
erDiagram
    BOOK {
        int id
        string title
        string author
        string isbn
        int publicationYear
    }

    USER {
        int id
        string name
        string email
        string membershipNumber
    }

    LOAN {
        int id
        date loanDate
        date returnDate
    }

    BOOK ||--o{ LOAN : "is loaned in"
    USER ||--o{ LOAN : "borrows"

    Diagram 2 — Sequence diagram voor REST API
    sequenceDiagram
    participant App as Bibliotheek App
    participant API as REST API
    participant DB as Database

    App->>API: GET /books
    API->>DB: Query all books
    DB-->>API: Return book list
    API-->>App: JSON list of books

    App->>API: POST /loans
    API->>DB: Insert new loan
    DB-->>API: Loan created
    API-->>App: 201 Created

    Diagram 3 — Use-case diagram voor bibliotheekgebruikers
    graph TD
    User((Gebruiker))
    Librarian((Bibliothecaris))

    User --> |Zoekt boeken| SearchBooks
    User --> |Leent boek| BorrowBook
    User --> |Retourneert boek| ReturnBook

    Librarian --> |Voegt boek toe| AddBook
    Librarian --> |Beheert leden| ManageUsers

    Diagram 4 — Extra diagram: State machine voor een boek
    stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Available
    Available --> Loaned : user borrows
    Loaned --> Returned : user returns
    Returned --> Available